Class GitScmPluginImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.azyva.dragom.model.plugin.impl.NodePluginAbstractImpl
      • org.azyva.dragom.model.plugin.impl.ModulePluginAbstractImpl
        • org.azyva.dragom.model.plugin.impl.GitScmPluginImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.azyva.dragom.model.plugin.ModulePlugin, org.azyva.dragom.model.plugin.NodePlugin, org.azyva.dragom.model.plugin.ScmPlugin

    public class GitScmPluginImpl
extends ModulePluginAbstractImpl
implements org.azyva.dragom.model.plugin.ScmPlugin
    ScmPlugin implementation that supports Git repositories using the git command line client installed locally.

    Credential handling is supported for the HTTP[S] protocol.

    No credential handling (private key) is supported for the SSH protocol. It is up to the user to correctly setup his git command line client.

    Author:
    David Raymond
